inistration?

Tara: I=E2=80=99m told he=E2=80=99s not going into the administration. He w=
as always a hired gun. He could run a super PAC for Trump. You make more mo=
ney on the outside, that=E2=80=99s for sure.

Peter: So who will be the R.N.C. chairman in this world?

Tara: I think Michael Whatley gets to stay R.N.C. chairman because they won=
=2E It=E2=80=99s the Democrats we should be talking about.

Peter: Right now, it doesn=E2=80=99t feel like the Resistance 2.0 is anywhe=
re close to coming into view. You just get the vibe that Democrats know the=
y lost and they don=E2=80=99t know how to come back. Rahm Emanuel called me=
 ( https://puck.news/the-missing-resistance-the-tao-of-rahm-emanuel/?utm_ca=
mpaign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2811%2F12%2F24%29&utm_so=
urce=3Dcustomer.io ) from Tokyo to talk about this. As you know, he=E2=80=
=99s the ambassador to Japan, but also a Democratic strategist at heart. He=
 echoed what a lot of Democrats have been saying, which is that Democrats h=
ave to get back to the basics, talking about the economy and listening to p=
eople and not be afraid to punch left at the identity politics that have co=
nsumed the national Democratic Party.

He told me, =E2=80=9CIf you decide to do identity politics, it gives the ot=
her side permission to do identity politics. Their identities are a majorit=
y in this country, not ours. Identity politics on its face is strategically=
 bankrupt.=E2=80=9D Democrats, to me, feel like they have to stand for some=
thing other than being against Donald Trump.

Tara: On my podcast, Somebody=E2=80=99s Gotta Win, I spoke ( https://open.s=
potify.com/episode/1Xf82JLsnluUzsjcd9ckwQ?si=3DpAcp7cz_QCS0Npi-UoV3Og&utm_c=
ampaign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2811%2F12%2F24%29&utm_s=
ource=3Dcustomer.io ) with Evan Roth Smith from Blueprint Polling. They had=
 some data on why voters did not want to vote for Kamala Harris, and he mak=
es some really interesting points. For instance, she lost Latinos over the =
debt, fiscal spending, and immigration. Like you said, they tried to create=
 divisions, or segment the voter population through identity politics, when=
 everybody was voting about the same thing: higher prices, feeling broke.

